node.text:
I wanted to create one last summer inspired dessert all about coconut and vanilla!
It is composed with a coconut Joconde sponge soaked with a Malibu and rum syrup, a coconut long lasting foam.
Inside the Pearl there is a vanille coconut coulis, a coconut cremeux and a light coconut mousse.
The whole dessert is trapped in a very thin layer of white chocolate.

I really wanted to focus an incredible amount of time working on the taste for this creation.
It is composed with a crunchy sweet dough, a moist peach sponge, a sous vide slow cooked (16 hours) peach compote, and a light peach mousse.
The rest of the ensemble is crafted out of thin layers of white chocolate!

node.text:
I wanted to create one last summer inspired dessert all about coconut and vanilla!
It is composed with a coconut Joconde sponge soaked with a Malibu and rum syrup, a coconut long lasting foam.
Inside the Pearl there is a vanille coconut coulis, a coconut cremeux and a light coconut mousse.
The whole dessert is trapped in a very thin layer of white chocolate.

It was about time I do a proper video of this little guy!
It is composed with a crunchy caramel base, a moist caramel sponge  holding a soft passion fruit cremeux and surrounded by a fluffy caramel marshmallow, the core of the head is a super tender passion fruit coulis trapped in a soft caramel cremeux and a very light caramel mousse, the whole thing dipped in a thin layer of a crunchy milk chocolate.
